# Quran Offline Replacement — Implementation Plan

Replace the live `quran.com` API calls with a self-contained, offline Quran data
system modeled after the **Quran Android** architecture described in
`QURAN_ANDROID_REFERENCE.md`. The app's existing UI, navigation, ViewModel, and
Room database layer remain untouched; only the data-supply path changes.

---

## Background

### Current architecture (online only)

```
QuranListScreen / SurahReaderScreen
    └─ QuranViewModel / SurahReaderViewModel
           └─ CompanionRepository → QuranRepository (interface)
                  └─ RealQuranRepository
                         ├─ QuranApi (Retrofit → quran.com API v4)
                         └─ CompanionDao (Room cache)
```

**Pain points with the current approach:**

| Problem | Impact |
|---|---|
| Surah list requires internet on first launch | App unusable offline |
| Ayah text/audio fetched per surah, per reciter from API | Slow; fails without network |
| `cached_surahs` table populated from API JSON | Fragile; breaks on API changes |
| Audio URLs come from `quran.com` CDN | Streaming only; no offline playback |

### Target architecture (offline-first)

```
QuranListScreen / SurahReaderScreen
    └─ QuranViewModel / SurahReaderViewModel  (unchanged)
           └─ CompanionRepository → QuranRepository (interface, unchanged)
                  └─ OfflineQuranRepository          ← NEW
                         ├─ MadaniDataSource          ← NEW (hardcoded arrays)
                         ├─ QuranInfo                 ← NEW (business logic)
                         └─ CompanionDao              (unchanged, cache for ayah text)
                                └─ assets/quran_text.json  ← NEW (bundled Arabic text)
                                   assets/translations/en_sahih_international.json ← NEW
```

