## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Audio strategy**: The Quran Android reference defines two audio models —
> *gapless* (per-sura MP3 + timing DB) and *gapped* (per-ayah MP3). The current
> app streams per-ayah URLs from `quran.com`. Which do you prefer post-migration?
>
> **Option A — Keep streaming** from quranicaudio.com per-ayah URLs (no download,
> but still requires internet for audio).  
> **Option B — Gapless streaming** via `https://download.quranicaudio.com/quran/{reciter}/{sura:03d}.mp3`
> (one file per sura, matches Quran Android's built-in reciters: Minshawi, Husary,
> Basfar).  
> **Option C — Full offline audio** (download sura MP3s to device storage, like
> the Quran Android app does).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Translation source**: Will you bundle a translation JSON asset in the APK, or
> keep fetching translations from an online API? Bundling is recommended for
> offline-first, but increases APK size (~2–3 MB for one English translation).

> [!NOTE]
> **Arabic text source**: The full Uthmani text (~1.5 MB JSON) would be bundled
> as an asset. The first launch will parse and seed Room; subsequent launches use
> the DB cache. Accepted?

