#### [NEW] `data/quran/QuranDataSource.kt`
Interface definition matching the reference (section 2.1). Acts as the single
source of truth for structural Quran data.

#### [NEW] `data/quran/SuraAyah.kt`
Simple data class `SuraAyah(val sura: Int, val ayah: Int)` as referenced in
section 1.1. Used by `quartersArray`.

#### [NEW] `data/quran/QuranInfo.kt`
Business logic class (section 4). Injected with `MadaniDataSource`. Exposes:
- `getPageNumberForSura(sura)` → O(1)
- `getSuraOnPage(page)` → O(1)
- `getFirstAyahOnPage(page)` → O(1)
- `getJuzFromPage(page)` → O(30)
- `getNumberOfAyahs(sura)` → O(1)
- `isMakki(sura)` → O(1)
- `getListOfSurahWithStartingOnPage(page)` → for juz/page navigation
- `getAyahId(sura, ayah)` → global ID

#### [NEW] `data/quran/SurahMetadata.kt`
Hardcoded list of all 114 surahs — names (transliteration), Arabic names,
English meanings, ayah counts, and Makki/Madani flags — derived from
`numberOfAyahsForSuraArray`, `isMakkiBySuraArray`, and section 7.2/7.3/7.4 of
the reference. This replaces the `Chapter` API model.

```kotlin
data class SurahMetadata(
    val number: Int,
    val nameTranslit: String,   // e.g. "Al-Fātihah"
    val nameArabic: String,     // e.g. "الفَاتِحَةِ"
    val meaning: String,        // e.g. "The Opening"
    val ayahCount: Int,
    val isMakki: Boolean,
    val juz: Int,               // computed via QuranInfo
    val page: Int               // first page, from pageForSuraArray
)
```

