### Layer 6 — Audio URL Strategy (New)

#### [NEW] `data/quran/QuranAudioUrlBuilder.kt`

Replaces the fragile `quran.com` CDN URLs with predictable quranicaudio.com
URLs that follow the Quran Android pattern. This keeps audio *streaming* (no
download needed), but uses stable, well-known CDN endpoints.

**Reciters to map** (keep current `SurahReaderViewModel.recitersList` IDs):

| Current ID | Quran Android equivalent | Gapless URL pattern |
|---|---|---|
| `ar.alafasy` | Mishari Alafasy (gapless) | `https://download.quranicaudio.com/quran/mishaari_raashid_al_3afaasee/{sura:03d}.mp3` |
| `ar.abdulbasitmurattal` | Abdul Basit Murattal | `https://download.quranicaudio.com/quran/abdul_baset/murattal/{sura:03d}.mp3` |
| `ar.husary` | Husary (gapless) | `https://download.quranicaudio.com/quran/mahmood_khaleel_al-husaree/{sura:03d}.mp3` |
| `ar.minshawimujawwad` | Minshawi (gapless) | `https://download.quranicaudio.com/quran/muhammad_siddeeq_al-minshaawee/{sura:03d}.mp3` |

> [!NOTE]
> For **gapless** streaming, one sura MP3 is played from start, and we no
> longer need per-ayah audio URLs. The existing `ExoPlayer` in
> `SurahReaderViewModel` will play the full sura file; the `playNextAyah()`
> auto-advance logic is replaced by simply letting the file play through.
> Per-ayah seek will need a timing database (a separate upgrade, not in scope
> of this plan).

